race.comment: A competitive feature. SEVEN'S (5) was an easy 70 winner at Rosehill and then was switched south by the Archibalds and did a good job from the back beaten 2.4L in an 84 at Flemington. Looks cherry ripe for this suitable assignment and can bounce back. SAVILLA (8) won by a space at Mornington before a 2L defeat at Moonee Valley in a 70, both against her own sex. The latest stacks right up, and she's been kept up to the mark with a sharp Flemington jumpout. Draws low and she's a threat. CABLE DANCER (4) came from back on cornering and hit the line strongly to score over 2200m at Ararat last time out. One of the main contenders. STATION ONE (7)  peaks and will be around the mark if he puts his best foot forward. LE ZEBRA (1) brings an easy Open win from the country, and fitter he can build on that.
